A monolithic application contains all functionality within a single codebase, whereas a microservices application divides functionality into multiple independent services.

Comparison:

* Monolithic

  * Easier initially
  * Single deployment
  * Difficult to scale individual components

* Microservices

  * Independent deployments
  * Better scalability
  * Improved fault isolation
  * Higher operational complexity

For example, a startup may begin with a monolithic application and later migrate to microservices as user traffic grows.

A real-life use case is large retail companies modernizing legacy applications for better scalability.

Choosing the appropriate architecture depends on application size, team structure, and business requirements.
